data.description: As you enter the community, take a deep breath and relax. Welcome to the country!!    You could enjoy this every day... You will fall in love with this 2150 sq. ft. home sitting on 1.95 acres. The house was built in 2015 but the owners have updated and improved the entire house with new paint inside and out, enlarged patios, fencing for safety and privacy, and updated ceiling fans and lighting. It's better than new.     The custom home features ample natural light and an open floor plan that encourages everyone to gather for family activities. The kitchen is quite large with enough countertop space to accommodate many "cooks" in the Kitchen. The breakfast bar is perfect for communication with the cook, after-school snacks, and doing homework. It opens to the dining room, the breakfast room, and the great room. Imagine the yummy dinners for your extended family, friends and neighbors.    The front patio area is enclosed for privacy and safety for small children and pets.  It is ideal for morning coffee or evening iced tea or wine... Just rock and watch everyone play. A large back patio is available to watch the big game complete with "tailgate" food from the grill. The backyard is fenced, again for the safety of small children and pets. but has room for gardening (the greenhouse stays), a playscape, or even a pool. The property extends far beyond the fence to the fence that belongs to a huge ranch. You will need a couple of chairs at that fence to watch the cows,  the sunset, see the wildlife and look at the amazing stars. Walk the property (or check out the survey) to see how large the yard is. The owners placed a marker at the corners of the property next to the road.     Drive around the community to see that all of the lots are large, the views are unbeatable and the amenities will encourage outdoor family activities.
